The paper proposes two full-text indexes based on the suffix array, which are data structures commonly used in computer science for text indexing and search. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also focuses on improving pattern searches, which is a common task in information retrieval (cs.IR) and natural language processing (cs.CL). Additionally, the paper mentions compression techniques, which are often used in data storage and retrieval (cs.DB) and machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper discusses the time-space trade-off of the proposed indexes, which is a common topic in computational complexity (cs.CC).
